-- Multi-enum pin (GRADUATED 2026-06-10 from known-failing/): a SECOND
-- user enum decl. Before the multi-enum registry, enter_enum_decl
-- required (¬_user_enum_done) and this decl was silently dropped, then
-- loudly Exit(9); sample.ev has 31 enums — this was its primary
-- compile blocker. Now both enums build (one group, one
-- Z3_mk_datatypes batch) and the program runs.
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 0
import "stdlib/kernel.ev"
enum QOp = QPlus | QMinus
enum QW = QWrap(QOp) | QNone
claim main
    t ∈ QW = QWrap(QPlus)
    ok ∈ Bool = (t matches QWrap(_))
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨Exit(ok ? 0 : 1)⟩
